President Donald J. Trump recently met with German Chancellor Angela Merkel and business leaders from both American and German companies to discuss workforce development for 21st century jobs, particularly in manufacturing. The President emphasized the importance of having workforce development programs in place to ensure that American workers are prepared to fill the jobs being created across the country. The group discussed various innovative job-training programs and heard firsthand stories about how these programs are positively impacting American students and workers. President Trump expressed his commitment to embracing new and effective job-training approaches, such as online courses, high school curriculums, and private-sector investments, to prepare individuals for well-paying careers in trade, manufacturing, technology, and other sectors of the economy. Both President Trump and Chancellor Merkel agreed on the significance of deepening bilateral cooperation on vocational training to enhance growth and improve the lives of workers in both the United States and Germany.